ften had dreadful consequences, and how much the social and cultural world is inscribed within the practice of biological psychiatry. The book will interest historians of medicine, practicing psychiatrists, and everyone who knows or has seen what it's like to be in mental distress.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEsprit et corps. 0aMaladies mentalesxPhysiothérapiexHistoirex20e sièclexÉtats-Unis. 0aMaladies mentalesxTraitementxHistoirex20e sièclexÉtats-Unis. 0aMental illnessxPhysical therapyxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aMental illnessxPhysical therapyzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMental illnessxTreatmentxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aMental illnessxTreatmentzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMental illnessxTreatment. 0aMind and body. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520917934?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520917934423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520917934/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles